Time complexity basics :
-Linear search - O(n) worst case
  As it checks every value.

-Move Zeros - O(n) / space - O(1)

Reverse Array - Two pointer - O(n) / space O(1)

Time complexity measuers how time grow with input size.
O(1) = constant.
O(logn) = binary search
O(n) = single loop
O(n^2) = nested loop
O(n logn) = merge sort
O(2^n) = bad recurssion

Space complexity

O(1) → No extra structure
O(n) → Extra array or recursion stack
O(log n) → Recursive binary search stack